We offer an exciting opportunity to work with our fantastic Brisbane based
team to provide support to our clients using the COSTAR Tyre and Automotive
software.

** ABOUT US **

MICROHOUSE has been providing software for the Tyre & Automotive industries
for over 40 years. From humble beginnings in 1982 as a family business,
operating out of shared office space, Microhouse has grown into a leader in
our industry across Australia and New Zealand. We have stayed at the forefront
of technology services and continue to deliver on our promise to provide
successful, reliable business systems.

In 2001 we formed a partnership with COSTAR Computer systems and have
continued to offer our clients class leading software specific to the Tyre and
Automotive industry which allows us to offer software systems for tyre retail,
tyre wholesale, automotive workshop management, inventory control, purchasing
and bookkeeping. Review our website (www.costar.com.au) and Facebook page to
learn a little bit more about us.

** ABOUT THE ROLE **

Based in Brisbane, the Support Specialist role is a permanent full-time
position working with a close-knit team providing second and third level **
software ** support. We are ** NOT ** looking for a networking or hardware
guru, but rather a person that understands how (SQL) databases and
server/client software operate under the hood. Someone who has an interest in
computer languages but doesn't want to be full blown developer would be
perfect for the role.

Our support is provided by phone, email and video conferencing and covers
point of sale, inventory management, and financial queries to meet the growing
needs of our clients and to match the increasing capabilities of our software.

** The successful applicant will: **

  * Undertake a well-established and comprehensive in-house training program. 
  * Interact with clients ranging from small retail clients to large national companies. 
  * Provide effective and courteous second and third level software support via both electronic and phone correspondence. 
  * Record, track, and document help desk requests through to the final resolution. 
  * Identify, escalate, and triage requests to the next level of support in a timely manner. 
  * Troubleshoot Windows operating systems. 
  * Identify potential changes and system improvements to present to the team for consideration and implementation. 
  * Complete testing of software changes including the documentation of results. 
  * Update support documentation when required. 

